Description: Heavily corroded copper alloy fragment of a rectangular plate, pierced by a round hole near the middle, and gently bent on one side. The edge on this side, where the plate seems to have been welded to another element, is irregularly broken.
Bibliographic references: Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.74, p.184, pl.26)
